                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6302.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Saltillo</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Saltillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-21T13:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1913—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Governor Carranza has officially announced to me that he will conform with the
                    new administration at Mexico City. All opposition here abandoned. Railroads will
                    be opened at once. Perfect quiet prevails.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Holland</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
